article.headline: St. Francis, N.Y. 76, Manhattan 73, OT
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Jamaal Womack scored 21 points, including a 3-pointer with 1.5 seconds to play, to help St. Francis of New York snap its 12-game winless streak with a 76-73 overtime victory against Manhattan on Thursday night. Robert Hines had three points and Womack a jumper as St. Francis (1-12) scored five straight points for a 72-68 lead with 41 seconds to play. Manhattan (3-7) gained its only tie of the game when Jamel Ferguson hit a 3-pointer to make it 73-73 with 10 seconds to play. Alan Sheppard had 15 points for St. Francis, Hines added 13 and Marcus Williams had 10. Arturo Dubois led Manhattan with 20, and Darryl Crawford had 14 for the Jaspers, who lost their fifth consecutive game. The Terriers' win leaves Delaware and Iona as the only Division I schools without a win.
